gov.nih.ncats.molwitch.io

Class ChemicalReaderFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.ncats.molwitch.io.ChemicalReaderFactory

  • public final class ChemicalReaderFactory
extends Object
    Factory class that can create ChemicalReaders from various input sources. The factory methods will automatically determine the type of molecule encoding that was used and choose the appropriate decoder.
    Author:
    katzelda

    • Method Detail

      • newReader

        public static ChemicalReader newReader(byte[] molBytes)
                                throws IOException
        Create a new Reader that will read in the data from the given byte array. The entire byte array will be parsed.

        This is the same as {newReader(bytes, 0, bytes.length)

        Parameters:
        molBytes - the byte encoded molecule data to parse, usually a mol file or SMILES string.
        Returns:
        a new ChemicalReader, will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the data.
        NullPointerException - if molBytes is null.

        public static ChemicalReader newReader(File molFile)
                                throws IOException
        Create a new Reader that will read in the data from the given File.
        Parameters:
        molFile - the File encoding molecule data, usually a mol file or SMILES file. The File must exist.
        Returns:
        a new ChemicalReader, will never be null.
        Throws:

        NullPointerException - if molFile is null.
